library(readr)
library(dplyr)
library(lubridate)
library(ggplot2)

setwd("C:/Users/Imelda Trejo/Documents/Under_reporting_covid_fitting_MX")

source('code_functions.R')

# Leer los datos
df <- read_csv(
  "C:/Users/Imelda Trejo/Documents/Under_reporting_covid_fitting_MX/covid_data_clean.csv", 
  locale = locale(encoding = "latin1"), trim_ws = TRUE
)
dates <- read_csv(
  "C:/Users/Imelda Trejo/Documents/Under_reporting_covid_fitting_MX/MX_covid_dates.csv"
)


wave_name<-"Fourth"

param_stats <- read_csv(paste0(wave_name,"_wave_statistics_parameters.csv"))

# Lista de estados
estados <- unique(df$State)

# Función para extraer parámetros
get_param <- function(df, param_name, col_name) {
  as.numeric(df %>% filter(Parametro == param_name) %>% pull({{col_name}}))
}

# Parámetros fijos del modelo
recoverMean <- 15 # días
parGamma <- 1 / recoverMean
Delta <- 1
wave <- "Fourth" #"Fifth"

for (estado in estados) {
  # Obtener el periodo de análisis para el estado y ola seleccionados
  myDates <- dates %>%
    filter(State == estado, Wave_number == wave)
  
  if (nrow(myDates) == 0) next # Si no hay datos para ese estado y ola, saltar
  
  Date_initial <- as.Date(myDates$Date_initial[1], format = "%b-%d-%Y")
  Date_end     <- as.Date(myDates$Date_end[1],     format = "%b-%d-%Y")
  
  # Filtrar los datos principales para el estado seleccionado
  myData <- df %>% filter(State == estado)
  
  # Convertir la columna de fechas a tipo Date de forma robusta
  myData <- myData %>%
    mutate(Date_fixed = parse_date_time(Date, orders = c("b-d-Y", "Y-m-d", "d-b-Y")))
  
  # Filtrar por el rango de fechas de la ola
  myData_wave <- myData %>%
    filter(Date_fixed >= Date_initial & Date_fixed <= Date_end)
  
  if (nrow(myData_wave) == 0) next # Si no hay datos, saltar
  
  # Extraer Cases, Dates y Population
  Smooth_cases <- as.numeric(myData_wave$Smooth_cases)
  Cases <- as.numeric(myData_wave$Cases)
  Dates <- myData_wave$Date_fixed
  Population <- as.numeric(myData_wave$Population[1])
  
  # Parámetros del modelo
  I0 <- Cases[1]
  
  # Extraer parámetros para el estado actual
  params_state <- param_stats %>%
    filter(Estado == estado)
  
  par_median <- c(
    get_param(params_state, "Beta", Mediana),
    get_param(params_state, "ObservedFraction", Mediana)
  )
  par_low <- c(
    get_param(params_state, "Beta", HDI_lower),
    get_param(params_state, "ObservedFraction", HDI_lower)
  )
  par_upper <- c(
    get_param(params_state, "Beta", HDI_upper),
    get_param(params_state, "ObservedFraction", HDI_upper)
  )
  
  # Model predictions
  mu_median <- MuK(par_median, Population, I0, Cases, parGamma, Delta)
  mu_low    <- MuK(par_low,    Population, I0, Cases, parGamma, Delta)
  mu_upper  <- MuK(par_upper,  Population, I0, Cases, parGamma, Delta)
  
  # Crear el nuevo data frame
  df_wave <- data.frame(
    Cases = Cases,
    Smooth_cases=Smooth_cases,
    mu_median = mu_median,
    mu_low = mu_low,
    mu_upper = mu_upper,
    Dates = Dates,
    Population = Population
  )
  
  
print(
  ggplot(df_wave, aes(x = Dates)) +
    # Banda de credibilidad (HDI)
    geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = mu_low / Population, ymax = mu_upper / Population, fill = "Credible interval"), alpha = 0.4) +
    # Línea del modelo (mediana)
    geom_line(aes(y = mu_median / Population, color = "Model median"), size = 1) +
    # Puntos de casos observados
    geom_point(aes(y = Cases / Population, color = "Observed cases"), size = 1.2) +
    # Puntos de casos suavizados
    #geom_point(aes(y = Smooth_cases / Population, color = "Smooth cases"), size = 1.2) +
    # Escalas y leyendas personalizadas
    scale_color_manual(
      name = "Legend",
      values = c("Observed cases" = "black", "Model median" = "blue")
    ) +
    scale_fill_manual(
      name = "Legend",
      values = c("Credible interval" = "skyblue")
    ) +
    labs(
      title = paste("Model fit and 95% Credible interval for", estado, "-", wave, "Wave"),
      x = "Date",
      y = "Cases / Population"
    ) +
    theme_minimal() +
    theme(
      legend.position = "top"
    )
)
  
  }
